flowRoot.flowPara: OS upgrades behave the same whether automatic updates are on or off. In other cases, update actions are replaced by download actions. If the update can be installed live it happens immediately after the download has completed. Otherwise, a separate install step is required.

We check for updates for every type of update except for packages, and notify the user when they're available. In the package case, checking for updates is expensive, so the check needs to be manually performed by the user. We probably need to provide reminders to do this.
Progress information is shown for software that's being downloaded. If it's waiting to be downloaded, the status reads "Download pending".
Automatic updates can be turned off by the user. They are also automatically disabled when on a mobile or metered connection.
